These prisons were designed to keep people in, not keep viruses out; COVID-19 has breached several facilities with deadly effect.
The virus is a public health crisis that threatens not only prisoners but also correctional facility workers and the neighboring communities.
Dr. Anthony Fauci and Dr. Deborah Birx were spot-on when they called for social distancing.
We can also translate social distancing within the context of criminal justice reform.
And we can be smart on COVID-19 by being smarter on those who are detained and who cannot practice social distancing.